data.title: Photos:: 50 most beautiful female celebrities
data.text:
Where youve seen her: She was Dr. Remy Hadley on the eight-season TV show House, but you probably know her as Thirteen Why we love her: Shes a pretty face on television, but shes also known for her charity work with Artists for Peace and Justice, Doctors Without Borders and her PBS documentary series called Half the Sky. (Al Seib / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: She played Brad Pitts mother in The Curious Case of Benjamin Button, Tyreses wacky love interest in Baby Boy and the independent woman in Think Like a Man Why we love her: Shes beautiful but her talent has earned many awards and award nominations for an Oscar and Emmy, too. (Kirk McKoy / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: On the big screen as a good vamp in the Twilight series Why we love her: Shes the bubbly, optimistic vamp in the Twilight series -- which is a nice change from the angst-fest we get from the rest of the fanged ones! (Jay L. Clendenin / Los Angeles Times)

Why you know her: Fans of the Bill Cosby spinoff show will remember her as Lena James on A Different World, but shes also known for the voice of Gloria on Madagascar, Niobe on The Matrix Revolution and her TV show Hawthorne Why we love her: Shes married to rapper/actor Will Smith but has a love for rock with her band Wicked Wisdom. She can act, dance and is the free-spirited mother of child actors Willow and Jaden Smith. (Kirk McKoy / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: On her reality shows Keeping Up With the Kardashians and Kim and Kourtney Take Miami, and at every red carpet known to man Why we love her: Shes a woman who knows what she wants (endless attention), and knows how to get it. Shes also rapper Kanye Wests better half. (Gina Ferazzi / Los Angeles Times)

Why you know her: You may remember her as the kid actor starring alongside Samuel L. Jackson in Eves Bayou or her later work in Think Like a Man, Waist Deep and TV show Deception Why we love her: Shes clearly drinking from the fountain of youth and can easily play the college girlfriend in movies like Stomp the Yard and turn around and hop stairs and fight as an undercover cop. Shes also giving the thumbs up for abstinence before marriage, which she did until she married her husband DeVon Franklin. (Carolyn Cole / Los Angeles Times)

Why you know her: She kissed a girl, liked it and she sang about it Why we love her: The cheeky singer and songwriter knows how to make a splash, both with her music and on the red carpet. (Jay L. Clendenin / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: On the big screen in Slumdog Millionaire Why we love her: Pinto burst onto the scene with Slumdog Millionaire, her first feature film. People magazine placed her on their Most Beautiful People List and List of the Worlds best Dressed Women. We couldnt agree more. (Dimitrios Kambouris / Getty Images)

Where youve seen her: She was in the underrated film Losers, but shes clearly no loser. You may know her from the bridge of the starship Enterprise in the new Star Trek reboot. Why we love her: Shes Lt. Uhura 2.0! Were geek enough to find that unbearably hot. (Al Seib / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: Dont pronounce Ling with a hard L on Ally McBeal or she will give you the stink eye. Or, maybe you recognize her as Dr. Joan Watson on Elementary, Viper on Kung Fu Panda and Officer Jessica Tang on Southland Why we love her: She always makes being a rebel sexy. (Jay L. Clendenin / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: On screens both big and small ranging from Think Like a Man, Tyler Perrys Daddys Little Girls and Bring It On Why we love her: Weve adored Gabrielle since Bring It On, but our respect for her skyrocketed when she testified to the Senate Judiciary Committee, sharing her own horrific story of rape, in support of the Violence Against Women Act. Shes also the better half of Miami Heat basketball player Dwyane Wade. (Brian van der Brug / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: On the arm of President Barack H. Obama and in just about every fashion magazine and blog there is Why we love her: We havent seen this much fashion sense since Jackie Kennedy Onassis. FLOTUS has not only been a fashion icon but shes the brains behind the Lets Move campaign to fight childhood obesity. (Michael Loccisano / Getty Images)

Where you know her from: Every single radio ever Why we love her: Shes cute as a button and she weathered many a storm this year. Some girls grow resentful of the ex-boyfriend but Taylor gets rich off of breakups. (Wally Skalij / Los Angeles Times)

Why you know her: Youve heard one of her many Grammy-winning hits on the radio. Shes also the wife of hip-hop producer Swizz Beatz. Why we love her: For all those hits, for piano playing, and most of all, for Keep a Child Alive -- a charity she co-founded that provides medicines to families with HIV and AIDS in Africa. (Gina Ferazzi / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: On the big screen Why we love her: She kicked butt in Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon, enchanted in Memoirs of a Geisha, showed off her tap-dancing skills (no, really!) in Princess Raccoon, and was the youngest person ever to sit on the jury of the Cannes Film Festival. Plus, she survived Rush Hour 2 with her dignity intact! (STR / AFP/Getty Images)

Why you know her: She stole the hearts of both Ryan Gosling and Owen Wilson in The Notebook and Wedding Crashers, respectively. Why we love her: Have you seen her smile? Its dazzling. We cant wait to see her got toe-to-toe with Robert Downey Jr. in Sherlock Holmes. (Carolyn Cole / Los Angeles Times)

Where you know her from: The competitive arenas of wrestling and dance

Why we love her: It takes guts to leap into the wrestling ring  and then leap onto the dance floor of Dancing with the Stars. Plus, there are her nicknames: The legs of the WWE and The Weapon of Mass Seduction (Michael Buckner / Getty Images for ELLE)

Where youve seen her: On runways, in magazines and hosting Project Runway

Why we love her: Klum has been stalking the catwalk since 1992, but shes hardly just a pretty face (and smokin bod). She won a Peabody award for Project Runway, for which she is host and executive producer. Thats the first Peabody award to a reality show. (Jay L. Clendenin / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: On the silver screen, including an Oscar-winning turn in Vicky Cristina Barcelona and Anna in To Rome With Love

Why we love her: Have you seen Vicky Cristina Barcelona? How about all her roles in Pedro Almodvars films? How can you not love a woman with that sort of talent? (Wally Skalij / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: On That 70s Show, Forgetting Sarah Marshall and as the funny but heart-on-her-sleeve love interest in Friends With Benefits

Why we love her: Yes, shes cute as a button. Yes, shes super talented. But we really love her the most because 1) shes the voice of Meg in Family Guy, and Family guy equals instant adoration, and 2) shes admitted shes a huge fan of World of Warcraft. (Jay L. Clendenin / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: Shes been on countless runways, was a Victorias Secret model and is the producer of Americas Next Top Model

Why we love her: She knows all things fierce. Shes tapped into every form of entertainment there is, from acting (Higher Learning and Love & Basketball), charity work (TZONE Foundation) to singing and modeling. (Dimitrios Kambouris / Getty Images)

Why we love her: Shes a gorgeous woman who refuses to fix what others may see as flaws  I have the hugest overbite. Its so big, my older brothers and sisters used to call me Bugs. I looked like a bottle opener. But Ive never fixed my bite because its one of the things that makes me me...My best feature is my big hips. Ive got some nice childbearing hips, and I feel very proud of them. When I was younger I thought they were too big. I wanted to be slimmer. But now I totally embrace them. (Kirk McKoy / Los Angeles Times)

Why you know her: Shes an Academy-Award-winning actress.

Why we love her: Her Oscar-winning performance in Monster was called one of the greatest performances in the history of the cinema by critic Roger Ebert. Plus shes passionately committed to helping the people of her native South Africa -- her foundation provides health services for some of the poorest regions of the country. (Al Seib / Los Angeles Times)

Where youve seen her: You either laugh, cheer her on or both while watching her as Mrs. Smith on Mr.and Mrs. Smith

Why we love her: As much as she loves kids, we should love her for that alone. Shes the right-hand woman of actor Brad Pitt, but she is a business woman and philanthropist all her own. Outside of acting, her charity work includes UNICEF, ONE Campaign and UNHCR. (Al Seib / Los Angeles Times)

Why you know her: Shes the go-to geek-bait hot babe, and has appeared on countless magazine covers

Why we love her: This quote from The Times of London, when the reporter asked her if she considered herself a role model: It depends on what your idea of a role model is. If your idea of a role model is somebody whos gonna preach to your kids that sex before marriage is wrong and cursing is wrong and women should be this and be that, then Im not a role model. But if you want your girls to feel strong and intelligent and be outspoken and fight for what they think is right, then I want to be that type of role model, yeah. (Al Seib / Los Angeles Times)

Why you know her: She broke big with Lost in Translation and hasnt slowed down since.

Why we love her: Shes a star who doesnt starve herself, doesnt advertise her personal business, and stays out of the tabloids. Plus, shes about to kick Iron Mans butt as the Black Widow! (Carolyn Cole / Los Angeles Times)

Where you know her from: Music, movies, awards shows.... where havent you seen her? Shes a new mom of her daughter Blue Ivy and the wife of rap star Jay-Z. She was also given the title as Peoples 2012 Worlds Most Beautiful Woman.

Why we love her: So many reasons, but mostly because Single Ladies is a song were almost glad will be stuck in our heads for the rest of our lives. Shes also no stranger to charity work, with Survivor Foundation being the most well-known for her contribution to Hurricane Katrina victims. (Jay L. Clendenin / Los Angeles Times)
